<TITLE> 4 robbers beaten to death by mob in Ctg </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Aug 29 (bdnews24.com)  Four robbers were beaten to death by a mob at Sitakundu in Chittagong early Saturday, police said. Sitakundu police chief Nazrul Islam told bdnews24.com that an armed gang of eight to ten robbers entered Sedai Nagar village of Bariardhala union. Locals, alerted to their presence, descended on the gang and beat them up, Islam said. "Four were left dead on the spot," said the police officer. Of the dead two were identified as Mohammad Bablu, 30, and Mohammad Younus, 35. Police also recovered two machetes, one Kirich, a locally made chopper and a knife from the spot, said Islam. A case was underway in this connection, he added. bdne
